This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition from human body skeletons. It also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, it involves video analysis, which makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of graph convolutional networks suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
